answer.text: "We were drawn to MacDonald's because they could accommodate younger riders, which wasn't an option at a number of other facilities.  We really enjoyed our ride through the desert - the horses were well trained and the guides were excellent offering up fun facts about horses and local wildlife along the way.  Prior to our ride we spent some time wondering the grounds. They tried to set up an "old town" but wondering through it mostly made me ponder if my Tetanus vaccines were up to date as some random items (scales, sewing machines, misc. metal) had been left to sit outside and weather the elements. They also had a small petting zoo as well as games. The main attraction is definitely the horse riding and I recommend MacDonald's for this activity."
answer.ctaText: See more reviews for this business.

reviewSnippet.answerPrompt: This is a review for museums in Phoenix, AZ:

answer.text: "Must see for kids and their grown-ups alike! The main attraction here are the Dinosaurs-- big as life and nearly as scary. In fact, you might want to give your kids a primer before visiting. We learned the hard way once when our five-year-old became so terrified we had to leave. (Bad Mom). The three-story Dinosaur Mountain, complete with thunder, a simulated flash flood and mechanical prehistoric creatures, is quite impressive.   Besides the dinos, there are several other fun attractions at the museum. What kid wouldn't want to pan for "gold," visit a (replica) Spanish Mission, or get locked in the authentic pioneer jail?   There are also two changing galleries and a gift shop."
answer.ctaText: See more reviews for this business.

answer.text: "I stopped by Mansel Carter Oasis Park with my son today for a play date with friends. This park is exceptional, the splash pad has activities for all ages and the water temperature is warm! The kids enjoyed playing in the water for a good long while before venturing up to the foam floored playground. The dry playground offers a great variety of activities including swings, slides, see saws, and even music instruments. The park has ample space for picnics and even a covered grilling area in the middle of the lake, which I might add has fish. Construction on the parks sport fields is still underway and looks extremely promising. My family looks forward to many future trips to this park!"

answer.text: "This store was a pleasant surprise.  A little hard to find, it's tucked away in a shopping area of some local tourist attractions, the Odysea Aquarium,  and the Butterfly House.   Look for the purple sign  that points to Four Peaks Mining, at the entrance.   The workers in the store were very enthusiastic, and friendly.  They were happy to talk about the many different fossils, and gemstones on display. The saleswoman was very helpful to me selecting an amethyst ring.  She didn't try to push more expensive items, just told me to get whatever ring I liked the best.  I appreciated the help, also the fact that the stones are from their local mine. It's definitely worth a visit to this store."
